com.pb.sawdust.calculator

Class PartialNumericFunctionN

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.calculator.NumericFunctionN
      • com.pb.sawdust.calculator.PartialNumericFunctionN

  • public class PartialNumericFunctionN
extends NumericFunctionN
    The PartialNumericFunctionN class provides a numeric function in which some arguments have be pre-specified. That is, this class wraps a NumericFunctionN and fills some of its arguments with values from a NumericValuesProvider. Thus, this class is similar to creating a curried function, and its argument count is the original function's minus the number of pre-specified values. The pre-specified arguments (from the base data provider) are not captured until the function is evaluated, so it is possible to build some dynamicsim into the "fixed" part of the evaluation of the function, through the use of an appropriate, mutating NumericValuesProvider.

    This class allows for the remaining arguments to be reordered as well, as it utilizes a mapping from its argument index numbers to those of the original function which is flexible in it application.

    • Constructor Detail

      • PartialNumericFunctionN

        public PartialNumericFunctionN(NumericFunctionN baseFunction,
                       int[] dimensionMap,
                       NumericValuesProvider baseProvider)
        Constructor specifying the base function, argument (dimension) mapping, and base values provider. The dimension map provides a mapping from the index of each argument of this function to the argument number of the base function. For example, if a base function takes three arguments, and a partial function based on it pre-specifies the second argument, then a possible dimension mapping would be 
             
     [0,2]
        which indicates that the first argument of the partial function maps to the first of the base function, and that the second argument of the partial function maps to the base's third argument.

        The base values provider must be of the same size as the number of arguments in the base function; the arguments/values in the dimension map will be ignored, but must be included.

        Parameters:
        baseFunction - The function this partial function is built from.
        dimensionMap - The mapping from this function's arguments to the (remaining) base function arguments.
        baseProvider - The values provider used to get the pre-specified arguments for the function.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the size of baseFunction and baseProvider are not equal, or if any of the indices in dimensionMap repeat or are out of bounds for the base function's arguments.
